<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Calculate and dump ThinLTO specific inliner stats.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The main statistics are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (1) Number of inlined imported functions,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (2) Number of imported functions inlined into importing module (indirect),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (3) Number of non imported functions inlined into importing module</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (indirect).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The difference between first and the second is that first stat counts</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// all performed inlines on imported functions, but the second one only the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// functions that have been eventually inlined to a function in the importing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// module (by a chain of inlines). Because llvm uses bottom-up inliner, it is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// possible to e.g. import function &#96;A&#96;, &#96;B&#96; and then inline &#96;B&#96; to &#96;A&#96;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// and after this &#96;A&#96; might be too big to be inlined into some other function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// that calls it. It calculates this statistic by building graph, where</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the nodes are functions, and edges are performed inlines and then by marking</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the edges starting from not imported function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// If &#96;Verbose&#96; is set to true, then it also dumps statistics</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// per each inlined function, sorted by the greatest inlines count like</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - number of performed inlines</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - number of performed inlines to importing module</span></CodeLine>
